# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Razorpay credentials — DO NOT COMMIT REAL VALUES (.env is gitignored)
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# This project's "backend" is Supabase Edge Functions (Deno), so the real
# secrets are NOT read from a local .env at runtime — they live as Supabase
# Edge Function secrets. Set them once with the Supabase CLI:
#
#   supabase secrets set \
#     RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=rzp_test_xxxxxxxxxxxxxx \
#     RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx \
#     --project-ref cuxblomxefwgdcijmpjk
#
# ...or in the dashboard: Project → Edge Functions → Manage secrets.
#
# The KEY_SECRET must NEVER reach the browser. The frontend only ever receives
# the KEY_ID, and it gets that from the razorpay-order function's response
# (order.key_id) — it is never hardcoded in frontend files.

# For local tooling / a future Node backend, copy this file to `.env`:
RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=rzp_test_xxxxxxxxxxxxxx
RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET=your_key_secret_here

# Frontend env-var prefixes (KEY_ID only — never the secret):
#   Vite:    VITE_RAZORPAY_KEY_ID
#   Next.js: NEXT_PUBLIC_RAZORPAY_KEY_ID
#   CRA:     REACT_APP_RAZORPAY_KEY_ID
